This paper discusses the construction of characteristic matrixes in covering information systems, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of matrixes also suggests a connection to linear algebra and machine learning, which are covered by cs.LG and cs.DS. Finally, the mention of computing and simplifying processes suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT).
